  "title": "Sales Executive (Commercial Vehicles)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Expand the clientele base</li>\n  <li>Indoor &amp; Outdoor Sales</li>\n  <li>Seek new clients and develop a clientele base</li>\n  <li>Follow up on potential prospects</li>\n  <li>Build and maintain rapport with new &amp; existing clients</li>\n  <li>Identify and pursue various business opportunities within the industry.</li>\n  <li>Follow up on cold calls to potential prospects.</li>\n  <li>Maintain good rapport with new or existing customers.</li>\n  <li>Achieve sales targets</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Compulsory Class 3 License</li>\n  <li>At least 1 year of relevant sales experience (Training will be provided)</li>\n  <li>Presentable, willing to learn, positive attitude, strong interpersonal skills, punctual, well-mannered, proactive, independent, resourceful and a high level of personal drive to succeed</li>\n  <li>Creativity<strong>:</strong> Think out of the box and effective problem-solving for the good of the company and colleagues</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>An attractive package featuring a generous base salary coupled with lucrative commission structures, a transportation allowance, and flexi benefits.</p>",
